latestPosts.caption:
Agar kisi cheez ko pure dil se chaho, toh poori kaaynaat usse tumse milane ki saazish mein lagjaati hai.

It all started when a skinny kid just wanted to stop being bullied for his physical appearance. All I wanted was to feel confident about my physique and have people see me for more than just my size. Growing up, the constant remarks about how I looked left a mark, but instead of letting it define me, I decided to change.

In 2017, I stepped into a gym for the first time. I didn’t know much back then, but I worked hard and began to see some results. It felt like I was finally on the right path. But then life took a turn. By 2020, I entered the worst phase of my life. My discipline faltered, and my habits changed for the worse. I gained weight rapidly, reaching 82 kgs with over 30% body fat. Looking in the mirror, I barely recognized myself—not just physically but mentally too. I felt lost.

In 2024, something within me reignited. I decided it was time to start over and take control of my life. This time, I wasn’t just doing it for appearance—I was doing it for my health, my confidence, and my peace of mind. With discipline, dedication, and determination, I went back to the gym and worked harder than ever before. Slowly but surely, I began to see progress. Every drop of sweat, every rep, and every disciplined meal brought me closer to my goal.

By April 2025, something incredible happened. For the first time in my life, I competed in a natural bodybuilding show at @icnindia an international level. Among 30 elite athletes from around the world, I placed 2nd and 4th Standing on that stage was more than just a moment of victory; it was proof that dreams do come true if you work for them.

A heartfelt thank you to the incredible people who made my transformation and the win possible  my mother, @alpha_ashwin01 and @sohaiil.mirza I owe everything to you three. Your unwavering support, guidance, and belief in me have been the driving force behind my journey. I wouldn’t be standing where I am today without you. Thank you from the bottom of my heart for everything you’ve done for me.

latestPosts.caption:
Some people walk into your life and leave a mark so deep that no words could ever truly capture it.
You are that person for me @alpha_ashwin01 

This was more than just a prep it was a journey filled with discipline, setbacks, growth, and countless silent battles.
None of this would have been possible without @alpha_ashwin01 you are not just my coach, but my mentor, my guide, and the one who believed in me even when I struggled to believe in myself.
You didn’t just train me you taught me how to fight, how to endure, and how to rise.
This medal belongs as much to you as it does to me.

You owned my journey like it was yours.
From every meal plan to posing corrections, every training session to tanning touch-ups you left nothing to chance.
You gave me your time, your energy, and your heart… and every moment of it shaped me.

A special thank you to you dada @daddy_biceps_ 
Those last five minutes of our backstage conversation completely shifted my mindset and gave me the confidence I needed before stepping on stage.
If we hadn’t had that talk, I truly believe I wouldn’t have even placed 5th.
As you said, “Raja sarkha jaaycha Ketan, ani raja sarkha perform karaycha.”

Thank you for believing in me when I couldn’t see my own strength @alpha_ashwin01 @daddy_biceps_ 
This stage, this transformation, this version of me  it’s a reflection of your belief, your efforts, and your heart.
I didn’t walk this journey alone  you were with me every step, and this achievement will always be ours.
Grateful beyond words today, tomorrow, and always.
